{
  "id": "feature-perf-001-route-lazy-loading",
  "title": "Route-Level Code Splitting with React.lazy",
  "category": "Performance",
  "description": "## Problem\nAll route components (BoardView, DashboardView, SettingsView, TerminalView, AgentView, etc.) are statically imported and bundled into the initial JavaScript payload. Despite TanStack Router having `autoCodeSplitting: true` in `vite.config.mts`, the route files use static imports which defeats code splitting. The generated `routeTree.gen.ts` imports all routes at the top level, meaning the entire app loads on first paint.\n\n## Current Behavior\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/board.tsx` does `import { BoardView } from '@/components/views/board-view'` (static)\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/dashboard.tsx` does `import { DashboardView } from '@/components/views/dashboard-view'` (static)\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/settings.tsx` does `import { SettingsView } from '@/components/views/settings-view'` (static)\n- Same pattern for all route files\n- `routeTree.gen.ts` (lines 11-27) imports all routes statically at the top level\n- `BoardView` alone is ~2,981 lines / ~125KB - all loaded immediately regardless of which page user visits\n\n## Required Changes\n1. Convert each route file to use `React.lazy()` with dynamic imports\n2. Wrap lazy components in `<Suspense>` with appropriate loading fallbacks using existing `<LoadingState>` component\n3. Add React error boundaries around lazy-loaded routes to handle chunk load failures gracefully\n4. Consider adding route preloading on hover/focus for perceived performance (TanStack Router supports `route.preload()`)\n5. Verify that TanStack Router's `autoCodeSplitting` works properly with the new lazy imports\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/board.tsx` - Convert to lazy loading\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/dashboard.tsx` - Convert to lazy loading\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/settings.tsx` - Convert to lazy loading\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/terminal.tsx` - Convert to lazy loading\n- `apps/ui/src/routes/project-settings.tsx` - Convert to lazy loading\n- All other route files in `apps/ui/src/routes/`\n- May need to add a shared `<ErrorBoundary>` component for chunk load failures\n\n## Pattern to Follow\n```tsx\n// BEFORE (board.tsx)\nimport { BoardView } from '@/components/views/board-view';\nexport const Route = createFileRoute('/board')({ component: BoardView });\n\n// AFTER (board.tsx)\nimport { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\nimport { LoadingState } from '@/components/ui/loading-state';\nconst BoardView = lazy(() => import('@/components/views/board-view').then(m => ({ default: m.BoardView })));\nexport const Route = createFileRoute('/board')({\n  component: () => (\n    <Suspense fallback={<LoadingState message=\"Loading board...\" />}>\n      <BoardView />\n    </Suspense>\n  ),\n});\n```\n\n## Expected Impact\n- Initial JS bundle reduced by 60-70% (major views won't load until navigated to)\n- Time-to-interactive improved significantly on first load\n- Each route becomes its own chunk, loaded on demand\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Each route loads its own JS chunk on navigation (visible in Network tab)\n- Loading states appear briefly during route transitions\n- No flash of unstyled content or layout shift\n- Chunk load failures show a friendly error with retry option\n- Route preloading on hover works for main navigation items\n\n## Reference\n- Good existing example: `terminal-panel.tsx` already uses dynamic imports for xterm\n- TanStack Router docs on code splitting: https://tanstack.com/router/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/code-splitting",
