    "content": "I'll start by exploring the codebase to understand the current route structure, then generate a comprehensive specification.\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:44:13.889Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore route files and structure\",\n  \"prompt\": \"Explore the route files and related components in apps/ui/src/routes/ to understand:\\n1. All route files and their current static imports\\n2. The routeTree.gen.ts file structure\\n3. The vite.config.mts autoCodeSplitting setting\\n4. The existing LoadingState component\\n5. Any existing error boundary components\\n6. The __root.tsx file structure\\n7. How TanStack Router is configured\\n\\nRead each route file fully. Also check apps/ui/src/components/ui/loading-state.tsx if it exists. Check for any existing Suspense or lazy usage in the codebase. Check apps/ui/src/app.tsx for router setup.\\n\\nBe very thorough - read all route files in apps/ui/src/routes/.\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:44:17.915Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore view components sizes\",\n  \"prompt\": \"Explore the view components to understand their sizes and import structures:\\n1. Check apps/ui/src/components/views/ - list all view files/directories\\n2. Read the main export of each view component (just the first ~30 lines to see exports)\\n3. Check if any views already use dynamic imports or lazy loading\\n4. Look at apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx to understand the BoardView component structure\\n5. Check apps/ui/src/components/ui/ for any loading-state component\\n6. Search for any existing ErrorBoundary components in the codebase\\n7. Check if there's a terminal-panel.tsx that uses dynamic imports as mentioned in the feature request\\n\\nBe thorough in exploring all view components.\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:44:20.369Z] 🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"C:/Users/DylanSmart/Downloads/automaker-pr/a