\\login.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:16.857Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\index.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:51.924Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\logged-out.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:52.549Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\github-issues.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:53.156Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\github-prs.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:53.541Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\ideation.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:53.965Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\interview.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:54.417Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\memory.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:58:54.913Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\notifications.tsx\"\n}\nNow let me check the routeTree.gen.ts and the vite config to understand the auto code splitting setup:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:59:35.741Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routeTree.gen.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:59:36.310Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\vite.config.mts\"\n}\nNow let me check the router utility and the terminal error boundary for the pattern we'll extend:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:59:51.678Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\utils\\\\router.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T19:59:52.862Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\terminal-view\\\\terminal-error-boundary.tsx\"\n}\nNow I have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive specification:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nAll 16 route components in the Automaker UI are statically imported, causing the entire application's view layer (~15,000 lines of component code) to be bundled into the initial JavaScript payload. Despite TanStack Router's `autoCodeSplitting: true` being enabled in `vite.config.mts`, every route file uses static ES6 imports that defeat code splitting. Users experience slower initial load times because components like `BoardView` (3,027 lines) and `TerminalView` (1,694 lines) are loaded regardless of which page is visited.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a **developer using Automaker**, I want **route components to load on-demand when I navigate to them**, so that **the initial page load is faster and I only download the code I need**.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- **Happy Path - Route Navigation**: GIVEN the app is loaded, WHEN a user navigates to `/board`, THEN the BoardView chunk is loaded on-demand and a loading spinner is shown briefly during the transition.\n- **Happy Path - Initial Load**: GIVEN a user opens the app for the first time, WHEN the initial page renders, THEN only the root layout and the initial route's chunk are loaded (not all 16 views).\n- **Happy Path - Subsequent Navigation**: GIVEN a user has already visited `/board`, WHEN they navigate away and return to `/board`, THEN the cached chunk loads instantly with no spinner.\n- **Edge Case - Slow Network**: GIVEN the network is slow, WHEN navigating to a new route, THEN a `LoadingState` spinner with a descriptive message is shown until the chunk loads.\n- **Edge Case - Settings Route with Search Params**: GIVEN the `/settings` route has `validateSearch` logic, WHEN lazy loading is applied, THEN the search parameter validation continues to work correctly.\n- **Error Handling - Chunk Load Failure**: GIVEN the network fails or a chunk is unavailable, WHEN navigating to a route, THEN a friendly error boundary is displayed with a \"Retry\" button that attempts to reload the chunk.\n- **Error Handling - Component Render Error**: GIVEN a lazy-loaded component throws during rendering, WHEN the error boundary catches it, THEN the user sees an error message with a retry option rather than a blank screen.\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | 16 route files in `apps/ui/src/routes/`, 1 new error boundary component, `routeTree.gen.ts` (auto-generated) |\n| Dependencies | React 19 (`lazy`, `Suspense`), `@tanstack/react-router` (already installed) |\n| Constraints | `routeTree.gen.ts` is auto-generated by TanStack Router Vite plugin - must not be manually edited; `settings.tsx` has `validateSearch` that must be preserved; `__root.tsx` should NOT be lazy-loaded (it's the shell) |\n| Patterns to Follow | Existing `TerminalErrorBoundary` pattern for error boundaries; existing `LoadingState` and `ErrorState` components for UI; existing `createFileRoute` pattern in all route files |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- **Refactoring view components** themselves (no breaking apart BoardView into smaller pieces)\n- **Adding route prefetching/preloading on hover** (can be done as a follow-up; TanStack Router supports `route.preload()` but that's a separate concern)\n- **Modifying `__root.tsx`** layout (the root route must remain eagerly loaded as it handles auth, theme, and layout)\n- **Modifying the auto-generated `routeTree.gen.ts`** (it will regenerate automatically when routes change)\n- **Adding loading skeletons per route** (the generic `LoadingState` spinner is sufficient for this iteration)\n- **Server-side rendering** or streaming (not applicable to this Electron/SPA app)\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Foundation - Error Boundary Component\n- [ ] T001: Create a reusable RouteErrorBoundary component for catching chunk load failures and render errors in lazy-loaded routes | File: apps/ui/src/components/ui/route-error-boundary.tsx\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation - Convert Route Files to Lazy Loading\n- [ ] T002: Convert board.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/board.tsx\n- [ ] T003: Convert dashboard.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/dashboard.tsx\n- [ ] T004: Convert settings.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary (preserve validateSearch) | File: apps/ui/src/routes/settings.tsx\n- [ ] T005: Convert terminal.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/terminal.tsx\n- [ ] T006: Convert project-settings.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/project-settings.tsx\n- [ ] T007: Convert spec.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/spec.tsx\n- [ ] T008: Convert setup.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/setup.tsx\n- [ ] T009: Convert index.tsx (WelcomeView) to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/index.tsx\n- [ ] T010: Convert login.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/login.tsx\n- [ ] T011: Convert logged-out.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/logged-out.tsx\n- [ ] T012: Convert github-issues.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/github-issues.tsx\n- [ ] T013: Convert github-prs.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/github-prs.tsx\n- [ ] T014: Convert ideation.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/ideation.tsx\n- [ ] T015: Convert interview.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/interview.tsx\n- [ ] T016: Convert memory.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/memory.tsx\n- [ ] T017: Convert notifications.tsx to use React.lazy with Suspense and RouteErrorBoundary | File: apps/ui/src/routes/notifications.tsx\n\n## Phase 3: Verification & Testing\n- [ ] T018: Run TypeScript build to verify no type errors from lazy loading changes | File: apps/ui/\n- [ ] T019: Run the full Vite build to confirm proper chunk splitting in the output | File: apps/ui/\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n| Metric | Measurement |\n|--------|-------------|\n| Separate chunks generated | Each route view produces its own JS chunk in `dist/assets/` (verifiable via `npm run build` output) |\n| TypeScript compiles cleanly | `npm run build` completes with no type errors |\n| Loading states visible | `LoadingState` spinner appears during route transitions on slow networks |\n| Error recovery works | `RouteErrorBoundary` renders retry UI when a chunk fails to load |\n| Settings search params preserved | `/settings?view=account` still navigates to the correct settings section |\n| No regressions | Existing E2E tests pass without modification |\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| TanStack Router `autoCodeSplitting` may conflict with manual `React.lazy` | We use `React.lazy` at the component level within the route's `component` property, which is compatible. The `autoCodeSplitting` flag affects route-level splitting which we complement, not replace. |\n| `routeTree.gen.ts` may regenerate and break lazy imports | Route files still export `Route` via `createFileRoute()` - the generated tree only imports route definitions, not view components. Lazy loading happens inside the component wrapper, not at the route definition level. |\n| Named exports require `.then(m => ({ default: m.X }))` wrapping | All view components use named exports. We'll consistently use the `.then()` pattern to convert them to default exports for `React.lazy`. |\n| Chunk load failures on flaky networks | `RouteErrorBoundary` with retry button handles this. The retry resets the error state and re-renders, triggering a fresh chunk load attempt. |\n| Flash of loading spinner on fast networks | TanStack Router's `defaultPendingMinMs: 0` is already set, and Suspense only shows fallback after a brief delay on fast connections. The spinner will rarely be visible on good connections. |",
